<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99788007156067></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99788007156067><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=3910&mid=99788007156067>a great weapon... and a great gift</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=3910&mid=99788007156067#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=85584><span id=Scholar>barfly</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>78 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Aug 15th 8:54 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.85]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>A good adventure and lesson, so bear with me...<br><br>Upon seeing that pallys get the best piercing weapons in the game, I decided that I should work on this skill as soon as possible.&nbsp;&nbsp;But I was dismayed to find out that almost all piercing weapons available to pallys come from Kunark or Velious, putting them beyond the reach of non-twinks until lvl 25 or so.  Yet I am determined to be the best pally I can be.<br><br>So at lvl 3 I went from Freeport to Fironia Vie in search of the worst (and hopefully, inexepensive) goblin eye poker (dmg 3, dly 18 -- good for newbie).  Thought there might be one at a merchant, but then realized when I got there that the higher-ups probably left those to rot rather than take up loot space.  But I did not give up.<br><br>Stayed there for four Earth days, logging on periodically to auction for a goblin eye poker.  Got some smart responses, and some puzzled queries as to what a lvl 3 was doing on Kunark (as though I had no right to wander into 'their' town).  But I persisted.<br><br>Struck up a conversation with a dwarf pally, Ernum (I think -- I forget names easily) from the Elite Clan on M. Marr server.  He understoood my dilemma, and as I was about to give up and go home, he said he would give me his Messenger of the Queen.  I gushed, and even tried to dissuade him from such a move (albeit half-heartedly), but he insisted.  I thanked him profusely, and when I mentioned that I purchased a tailored quiver while wandering around there, he made me a carved elm bow and gave me 80 hooked/bone arrows to boot!<br><br>The moral of the story is that initiative pays off, as does humility and respect for others.  Be gracious in accepting gifts, and conduct yourself with honor and dignity rather than begging at the local bank and people will show you more consideration.  I can't even remeber how many times I have given passed on nice newbie items only to have the player turn around and ask for more without saying thank you.  Just because you are classified as a 'newbie' does not mean you have to act like one. <br><br>Oh, the weapon is amazing.  Will use it until I get something better, and then I will pass it on to another pally newbie who knows how to play well with others.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
